Heat the olive oil in a small saucepan, add the onion, garlic and leek and saut√© for 4-5 minutes, or until softened but not coloured.Add the vegetable stock, milk and seasoning and bring to the boil. Simmer for six minutes, then remove from the heat and allow to cool slightly. Pour into a food processor and blend until smooth.To serve, pour into a bowl and garnish with a swirl of double cream and chopped chives.